'''Open Xange''' (formerly '''Xange''', '''Simplis''' and '''Vixta''') is a general-purpose [[Linux distribution]], based on [[Fedora (operating system)|Fedora]]. It is modelled as a replacement for [[Windows]], and uses [[Wine (software)|Wine]] to allow the user to run native Windows binaries.
